00:00:03.130 --> 00:00:05.730 align:middle line:84%
And I'd like to welcome you
to "Living in Balance" today.

00:00:05.730 --> 00:00:09.540 align:middle line:10%
We are going to learn how we
can maximize our potential.

00:00:09.540 --> 00:00:10.530 align:middle line:10%
I love it.

00:00:10.530 --> 00:00:12.540 align:middle line:10%
It is part of the
American dream.

00:00:12.540 --> 00:00:15.642 align:middle line:84%
Come join us, "Living in
Balance on Shakti-Hill."

00:00:15.642 --> 00:00:18.594 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:18.594 --> 00:00:36.840 align:middle line:90%


00:00:36.840 --> 00:00:40.150 align:middle line:90%
Andrew Wood is a success story.

00:00:40.150 --> 00:00:43.020 align:middle line:84%
And he is sharing his
success with other people.

00:00:43.020 --> 00:00:45.420 align:middle line:84%
There are techniques
that can help you

00:00:45.420 --> 00:00:47.160 align:middle line:90%
to share the American dream.

00:00:47.160 --> 00:00:49.080 align:middle line:90%
So, Andrew Wood, welcome.

00:00:49.080 --> 00:00:49.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Welcome to you.

00:00:49.880 --> 00:00:50.680 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS]

00:00:50.680 --> 00:00:51.930 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you for having me.

00:00:51.930 --> 00:00:54.180 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I'm really pleased
that you could come today.

00:00:54.180 --> 00:00:56.910 align:middle line:84%
Because I had talked
with you about your being

00:00:56.910 --> 00:01:00.900 align:middle line:84%
a motivational speaker because
you share so much positive,

00:01:00.900 --> 00:01:02.610 align:middle line:84%
as far as the message
that you have.

00:01:02.610 --> 00:01:04.349 align:middle line:84%
But you said you
really would rather

00:01:04.349 --> 00:01:08.230 align:middle line:84%
think of yourself as maximizing
potential within people.

00:01:08.230 --> 00:01:09.030 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:01:09.030 --> 00:01:11.670 align:middle line:84%
I think there's a lot
of negativity, perhaps,

00:01:11.670 --> 00:01:13.120 align:middle line:90%
or I don't know.

00:01:13.120 --> 00:01:15.390 align:middle line:84%
But when somebody
asks what do I do,

00:01:15.390 --> 00:01:17.310 align:middle line:84%
I never say I'm a
motivational speaker.

00:01:17.310 --> 00:01:20.910 align:middle line:84%
Because I'm not somebody that
will go in and hype somebody up

00:01:20.910 --> 00:01:21.960 align:middle line:90%
into feeling good.

00:01:21.960 --> 00:01:24.300 align:middle line:84%
What I really want to
do is make a difference

00:01:24.300 --> 00:01:27.600 align:middle line:84%
in somebody's life, to give
them some skills that they

00:01:27.600 --> 00:01:29.460 align:middle line:90%
can be a self-motivator.

00:01:29.460 --> 00:01:30.790 align:middle line:90%
So I'm a maximizer.

00:01:30.790 --> 00:01:33.780 align:middle line:84%
I try to help them get the
most out of themselves.

00:01:33.780 --> 00:01:36.240 align:middle line:90%
And that makes them motivated.

00:01:36.240 --> 00:01:39.540 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you know, everyone
out there has a potential.

00:01:39.540 --> 00:01:41.490 align:middle line:90%
And some are reaching it.

00:01:41.490 --> 00:01:44.040 align:middle line:84%
Most of us could really
do better, could we not?

00:01:44.040 --> 00:01:45.540 align:middle line:90%
I mean, we could be happier.

00:01:45.540 --> 00:01:46.750 align:middle line:90%
We could be more fulfilled.

00:01:46.750 --> 00:01:48.540 align:middle line:90%
We could be serving others more.

00:01:48.540 --> 00:01:52.680 align:middle line:84%
>> As Henry David Thoreau said,
most people live lives of quiet

00:01:52.680 --> 00:01:53.680 align:middle line:90%
desperation.

00:01:53.680 --> 00:01:57.450 align:middle line:84%
So, yes, most people seriously
underutilize the potential

00:01:57.450 --> 00:01:58.420 align:middle line:90%
they have in them.

00:01:58.420 --> 00:01:59.220 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:01:59.220 --> 00:02:02.010 align:middle line:10%
And they are not,
then, having any

00:02:02.010 --> 00:02:04.440 align:middle line:10%
of those wonderful
feelings that we have

00:02:04.440 --> 00:02:06.510 align:middle line:10%
when we are doing a good job.

00:02:06.510 --> 00:02:09.810 align:middle line:84%
Like my one sister had said,
that you feel so good when

00:02:09.810 --> 00:02:12.060 align:middle line:84%
you're contributing, and
when you are successful,

00:02:12.060 --> 00:02:14.880 align:middle line:84%
and you've made that sale
or you've done that thing.

00:02:14.880 --> 00:02:17.350 align:middle line:84%
That's a wonderful
motivator, just in itself.

00:02:17.350 --> 00:02:18.150 align:middle line:90%
Isn't it?

00:02:18.150 --> 00:02:19.900 align:middle line:84%
So there's kind of a
self-fulfilling part.

00:02:19.900 --> 00:02:23.040 align:middle line:84%
>> I think it's real motivation
rather than fake motivation.

00:02:23.040 --> 00:02:26.460 align:middle line:84%
When you are doing something
you're passionate about--

00:02:26.460 --> 00:02:29.220 align:middle line:84%
when you're doing something you
believe in, like you are doing

00:02:29.220 --> 00:02:31.950 align:middle line:84%
or like I'm doing, it's
easy to get excited

00:02:31.950 --> 00:02:36.223 align:middle line:84%
and to be really motivated, as
opposed to go into a seminar

00:02:36.223 --> 00:02:38.140 align:middle line:84%
or listening to tapes
and just kind of getting

00:02:38.140 --> 00:02:40.970 align:middle line:84%
jazzed up until you get back
home and have to pay the bills,

00:02:40.970 --> 00:02:41.770 align:middle line:90%
again.

00:02:41.770 --> 00:02:42.870 align:middle line:90%
>> But I loved your story.

00:02:42.870 --> 00:02:45.640 align:middle line:10%
Because you came to the United
States with a suitcase and $300

00:02:45.640 --> 00:02:46.440 align:middle line:10%
bucks.

00:02:46.440 --> 00:02:47.100 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:02:47.100 --> 00:02:47.900 align:middle line:90%
>> That's correct.

00:02:47.900 --> 00:02:50.820 align:middle line:84%
My 18th birthday present
was a one-way ticket

00:02:50.820 --> 00:02:52.760 align:middle line:90%
to America, $300.

00:02:52.760 --> 00:02:53.560 align:middle line:90%
>> That was it.

00:02:53.560 --> 00:02:53.710 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:02:53.710 --> 00:02:54.940 align:middle line:90%
>> That was it.

00:02:54.940 --> 00:02:57.550 align:middle line:84%
>> And then, you
have come a long way.

00:02:57.550 --> 00:02:59.370 align:middle line:84%
So you don't need to
brag about yourself.

00:02:59.370 --> 00:03:01.540 align:middle line:84%
But would you share with
us where you are right now,

00:03:01.540 --> 00:03:04.140 align:middle line:90%
what you have come since then?

00:03:04.140 --> 00:03:07.260 align:middle line:84%
>> I started out wanting to
become a golf professional.

00:03:07.260 --> 00:03:08.760 align:middle line:84%
And I was reasonably
good at golf.

00:03:08.760 --> 00:03:13.080 align:middle line:84%
But golf, as most major sports
are, was a very pointy pyramid.

00:03:13.080 --> 00:03:14.970 align:middle line:90%
And good was not good enough.

00:03:14.970 --> 00:03:18.330 align:middle line:84%
So lack of talent held me
back from fulfilling my dream

00:03:18.330 --> 00:03:19.770 align:middle line:90%
of being on the PGA TOUR.

00:03:19.770 --> 00:03:22.380 align:middle line:84%
But I got involved in
the karate business,

00:03:22.380 --> 00:03:24.750 align:middle line:84%
and over the last
10 years have built

00:03:24.750 --> 00:03:27.930 align:middle line:84%
one of the largest chains of
karate schools in the world.

00:03:27.930 --> 00:03:30.360 align:middle line:84%
And, in the process,
have got all the things

00:03:30.360 --> 00:03:32.460 align:middle line:84%
people would like to
get, such as the money

00:03:32.460 --> 00:03:33.960 align:middle line:90%
and the cars and the homes.

00:03:33.960 --> 00:03:35.560 align:middle line:90%
And it's been a lot of fun.

00:03:35.560 --> 00:03:36.360 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:03:36.360 --> 00:03:38.152 align:middle line:10%
Well, in talking with
your staff they said,

00:03:38.152 --> 00:03:39.840 align:middle line:10%
well, he'll drive
up in his Ferrari.

00:03:39.840 --> 00:03:41.970 align:middle line:84%
I thought, now, that
is a success story.

00:03:41.970 --> 00:03:45.060 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] So you're enjoying it.

00:03:45.060 --> 00:03:46.130 align:middle line:90%
>> I certainly am.

00:03:46.130 --> 00:03:46.470 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:03:46.470 --> 00:03:47.270 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:03:47.270 --> 00:03:50.820 align:middle line:84%
>> And I think, you know, a
mistake a lot of people make is

00:03:50.820 --> 00:03:54.630 align:middle line:84%
that in setting goals and
striving to do better,

00:03:54.630 --> 00:03:57.070 align:middle line:84%
they kind of give up
life in the process.

00:03:57.070 --> 00:03:59.910 align:middle line:84%
And I'd like to think that's
something that we haven't done

00:03:59.910 --> 00:04:02.670 align:middle line:84%
in our company and our
business, in that, yes,

00:04:02.670 --> 00:04:04.890 align:middle line:84%
we're very motivated
to help people

00:04:04.890 --> 00:04:07.470 align:middle line:84%
and to share our
books and our seminars

00:04:07.470 --> 00:04:09.300 align:middle line:84%
and our audio programs
with other people.

00:04:09.300 --> 00:04:11.460 align:middle line:84%
But the journey has
to be fun, as well.

00:04:11.460 --> 00:04:13.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:04:13.170 --> 00:04:15.214 align:middle line:90%
Now, the books and so forth--

00:04:15.214 --> 00:04:16.589 align:middle line:84%
you have a whole
series of tapes.

00:04:16.589 --> 00:04:21.329 align:middle line:84%
And we have a graphic on that,
that has some of the tapes.

00:04:21.329 --> 00:04:23.490 align:middle line:84%
And that's one of the
ways that you share.

00:04:23.490 --> 00:04:25.170 align:middle line:84%
And you get out in
front of the people.

00:04:25.170 --> 00:04:27.450 align:middle line:84%
But you said, it's not
enough just to hear it.

00:04:27.450 --> 00:04:31.050 align:middle line:84%
How nice it is if you
can reinforce that, too.

00:04:31.050 --> 00:04:35.260 align:middle line:10%
So you like to actually assist
people in different ways.

00:04:35.260 --> 00:04:36.060 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:04:36.060 --> 00:04:39.510 align:middle line:84%
My real passion in life is
to help people maximize.

00:04:39.510 --> 00:04:41.580 align:middle line:84%
And I do a lot of
seminars, a lot

00:04:41.580 --> 00:04:44.610 align:middle line:84%
of speaking for corporations
and associations.

00:04:44.610 --> 00:04:46.660 align:middle line:84%
But just doing it
one day isn't enough.

00:04:46.660 --> 00:04:49.260 align:middle line:84%
You can get somebody excited
and you can give somebody

00:04:49.260 --> 00:04:51.600 align:middle line:84%
some of the tools,
but we all know

00:04:51.600 --> 00:04:54.050 align:middle line:84%
that to make meaningful
change in our lives

00:04:54.050 --> 00:04:55.470 align:middle line:90%
it doesn't happen like that.

00:04:55.470 --> 00:04:57.390 align:middle line:84%
And so I've dedicated
the last couple

00:04:57.390 --> 00:05:01.530 align:middle line:84%
of years to really sitting down
and producing these products so

00:05:01.530 --> 00:05:03.630 align:middle line:84%
that people can go
home and continue

00:05:03.630 --> 00:05:05.820 align:middle line:84%
the process of learning
and discovering how

00:05:05.820 --> 00:05:07.200 align:middle line:90%
to maximize their potential.

00:05:07.200 --> 00:05:10.050 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, what we're finding
is that often negativity will

00:05:10.050 --> 00:05:14.080 align:middle line:84%
creep in to our thinking process
because of the outside world.

00:05:14.080 --> 00:05:15.480 align:middle line:84%
So we do have to
have techniques,

00:05:15.480 --> 00:05:18.708 align:middle line:84%
like affirmations or tapes that
we listen to, books that we--

00:05:18.708 --> 00:05:21.000 align:middle line:84%
we were just talking about
that, one of my staff and I.

00:05:21.000 --> 00:05:23.190 align:middle line:84%
And it really is
important to keep that up.

00:05:23.190 --> 00:05:27.150 align:middle line:84%
I asked you if you could
share with people on not just

00:05:27.150 --> 00:05:29.040 align:middle line:84%
the techniques that
are successful.

00:05:29.040 --> 00:05:30.480 align:middle line:90%
What are the blockages?

00:05:30.480 --> 00:05:33.180 align:middle line:10%
What keeps people
from being successful,

00:05:33.180 --> 00:05:37.130 align:middle line:10%
from feeling that wonderful
feeling of success

00:05:37.130 --> 00:05:38.385 align:middle line:10%
and positive thinking?

00:05:38.385 --> 00:05:40.010 align:middle line:84%
>> I think the greatest
thing, Georgia,

00:05:40.010 --> 00:05:43.340 align:middle line:84%
that holds most people
back is limitations--

00:05:43.340 --> 00:05:47.220 align:middle line:84%
mental limitations about what
they think they can or cannot

00:05:47.220 --> 00:05:48.020 align:middle line:90%
do.

00:05:48.020 --> 00:05:49.687 align:middle line:84%
And I think one of
my favorite stories--

00:05:49.687 --> 00:05:52.222 align:middle line:84%
I've just finished doing a
program with Brian Tracy called

00:05:52.222 --> 00:05:53.305 align:middle line:90%
"The Traits of Champions."

00:05:53.305 --> 00:05:56.390 align:middle line:84%
And it's a very interesting
program close to my heart

00:05:56.390 --> 00:05:58.760 align:middle line:84%
because what it is, is
how to succeed in life

00:05:58.760 --> 00:06:00.760 align:middle line:90%
told through golfing anecdotes.

00:06:00.760 --> 00:06:03.230 align:middle line:84%
And there's a story about
somebody actually very locally,

00:06:03.230 --> 00:06:04.910 align:middle line:90%
Calvin Peete.

00:06:04.910 --> 00:06:09.140 align:middle line:84%
At 24 years old, he'd never
played golf in his life.

00:06:09.140 --> 00:06:14.510 align:middle line:84%
He was one of 19 children, the
son of a migrant farm worker.

00:06:14.510 --> 00:06:16.335 align:middle line:84%
And he started playing
golf when he was 24.

00:06:16.335 --> 00:06:19.640 align:middle line:84%
He immediately decided he was
going to get on the PGA TOUR,

00:06:19.640 --> 00:06:25.580 align:middle line:84%
gave up farm working for $100
a week, and within 10 years

00:06:25.580 --> 00:06:27.710 align:middle line:84%
was the leading money
winner on the PGA TOUR.

00:06:27.710 --> 00:06:30.380 align:middle line:84%
And to date, he's
won $5 or $6 million.

00:06:30.380 --> 00:06:31.910 align:middle line:84%
He's playing on the
senior tour now.

00:06:31.910 --> 00:06:32.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Whoa.

00:06:32.710 --> 00:06:33.540 align:middle line:90%
>> Big dreams.

00:06:33.540 --> 00:06:36.290 align:middle line:84%
It's very important not to
let other people tell you

00:06:36.290 --> 00:06:37.470 align:middle line:90%
what you can or can't do.

00:06:37.470 --> 00:06:39.350 align:middle line:84%
You've got to dream
those big dreams.

00:06:39.350 --> 00:06:40.150 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:06:40.150 --> 00:06:41.630 align:middle line:90%
But there are certain--

00:06:41.630 --> 00:06:43.020 align:middle line:90%
there's a lot of hard work.

00:06:43.020 --> 00:06:46.070 align:middle line:84%
You didn't just get from
your suitcase and $300

00:06:46.070 --> 00:06:48.770 align:middle line:84%
to the position you are right
now without working hard.

00:06:48.770 --> 00:06:49.670 align:middle line:90%
Is that an element?

00:06:49.670 --> 00:06:51.878 align:middle line:84%
I mean, do we really have
to put the energy out there

00:06:51.878 --> 00:06:54.400 align:middle line:84%
but it doesn't feel like
work because we love it?

00:06:54.400 --> 00:06:55.550 align:middle line:90%
>> I think that's the key.

00:06:55.550 --> 00:06:58.520 align:middle line:84%
There's no doubt that be
successful in any field you

00:06:58.520 --> 00:07:00.620 align:middle line:84%
have to put out the hard
work, and the energy,

00:07:00.620 --> 00:07:02.450 align:middle line:90%
and the perspiration.

00:07:02.450 --> 00:07:05.780 align:middle line:84%
The key is to do something
that you love doing so

00:07:05.780 --> 00:07:08.285 align:middle line:90%
that it doesn't feel like work.

00:07:08.285 --> 00:07:10.940 align:middle line:84%
If I won the lotto
tomorrow, I keep

00:07:10.940 --> 00:07:14.160 align:middle line:84%
doing what I'm doing because
I love what I'm doing.

00:07:14.160 --> 00:07:15.500 align:middle line:90%
And that's really a key aspect.

00:07:15.500 --> 00:07:16.750 align:middle line:90%
>> That is the test, isn't it?

00:07:16.750 --> 00:07:18.542 align:middle line:84%
And that happens, it's
kind of interesting,

00:07:18.542 --> 00:07:20.870 align:middle line:84%
when someone has won the
lottery or something,

00:07:20.870 --> 00:07:23.450 align:middle line:84%
and they don't want
to give up their job.

00:07:23.450 --> 00:07:25.910 align:middle line:84%
They really have enjoyed
what they have been doing.

00:07:25.910 --> 00:07:28.460 align:middle line:10%
And that would be the
test, would it not?

00:07:28.460 --> 00:07:30.890 align:middle line:10%
>> I think it really is.

00:07:30.890 --> 00:07:33.020 align:middle line:84%
Would you keep doing
what you're doing now,

00:07:33.020 --> 00:07:34.310 align:middle line:90%
if you won the lottery?

00:07:34.310 --> 00:07:36.560 align:middle line:84%
If the answer to
that question is no,

00:07:36.560 --> 00:07:38.270 align:middle line:90%
then that tells you something.

00:07:38.270 --> 00:07:40.970 align:middle line:84%
>> But what about the person
who-- and this morning,

00:07:40.970 --> 00:07:43.340 align:middle line:84%
this happened with a
young man who called.

00:07:43.340 --> 00:07:47.390 align:middle line:10%
And he was talking
about he hated his job,

00:07:47.390 --> 00:07:50.000 align:middle line:10%
and he doesn't know whether
he can give that up because he

00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:51.630 align:middle line:10%
has a wife and he has a child.

00:07:51.630 --> 00:07:53.150 align:middle line:10%
So there is a
responsibility aspect.

00:07:53.150 --> 00:07:55.010 align:middle line:10%
Now, what do you
say to this man who

00:07:55.010 --> 00:07:58.790 align:middle line:10%
has a good, responsible
job with a secure income

00:07:58.790 --> 00:08:00.440 align:middle line:10%
but he doesn't like it?

00:08:00.440 --> 00:08:03.140 align:middle line:84%
>> That's a wonderful question
because that's the place where

00:08:03.140 --> 00:08:04.790 align:middle line:90%
so many people are.

00:08:04.790 --> 00:08:06.800 align:middle line:84%
So many people are
in a job they hate

00:08:06.800 --> 00:08:10.470 align:middle line:84%
or a business they don't like or
basically defending a position

00:08:10.470 --> 00:08:12.170 align:middle line:90%
they've had already taken.

00:08:12.170 --> 00:08:15.140 align:middle line:84%
And the way to do that is to
come up with a transitional

00:08:15.140 --> 00:08:17.270 align:middle line:84%
stage. , Obviously
somebody like that is--

00:08:17.270 --> 00:08:20.060 align:middle line:84%
the best thing for his family
is not going to be if he ups

00:08:20.060 --> 00:08:23.300 align:middle line:84%
and quits his lousy job and
goes and does something else.

00:08:23.300 --> 00:08:25.730 align:middle line:84%
So the key in
those situations is

00:08:25.730 --> 00:08:28.790 align:middle line:84%
to start transitioning
over to a plan B.

00:08:28.790 --> 00:08:30.500 align:middle line:84%
What could he do
in his spare time?

00:08:30.500 --> 00:08:32.000 align:middle line:90%
What could he do on weekends?

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:34.250 align:middle line:84%
Let's say he was
into model trains.

00:08:34.250 --> 00:08:35.809 align:middle line:84%
What could he do
at the swap meet

00:08:35.809 --> 00:08:37.659 align:middle line:90%
on the weekend to turn that--

00:08:37.659 --> 00:08:40.210 align:middle line:84%
and many of my
clients have turned

00:08:40.210 --> 00:08:43.940 align:middle line:84%
hobbies or secondary businesses,
doing them on nights,

00:08:43.940 --> 00:08:49.190 align:middle line:84%
doing them on weekends, into
full blown businesses a year

00:08:49.190 --> 00:08:50.520 align:middle line:90%
or two years down the line.

00:08:50.520 --> 00:08:51.770 align:middle line:90%
>> And if he is--

00:08:51.770 --> 00:08:54.140 align:middle line:84%
if it is his hobby and
he's really enjoying it,

00:08:54.140 --> 00:08:56.750 align:middle line:84%
then he won't mind putting
in those extra hours.

00:08:56.750 --> 00:08:57.800 align:middle line:90%
So that would make sense.

00:08:57.800 --> 00:08:59.160 align:middle line:10%
Whatever it is he loves to do--

00:08:59.160 --> 00:08:59.960 align:middle line:10%
>> Exactly

00:08:59.960 --> 00:09:00.955 align:middle line:10%
>> --that he could.

00:09:00.955 --> 00:09:03.080 align:middle line:84%
And just sort of look at
what is the market for it.

00:09:03.080 --> 00:09:05.870 align:middle line:84%
If he's a musician
or if he is an artist

00:09:05.870 --> 00:09:09.590 align:middle line:84%
or whatever and he'd like
to support himself totally

00:09:09.590 --> 00:09:11.930 align:middle line:84%
in that way, still,
he can be responsible

00:09:11.930 --> 00:09:13.503 align:middle line:90%
because he can just sort of--

00:09:13.503 --> 00:09:14.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Transition into it.

00:09:14.420 --> 00:09:15.070 align:middle line:90%
>> --make that transition.

00:09:15.070 --> 00:09:15.950 align:middle line:90%
>> And I think the other thing--

00:09:15.950 --> 00:09:18.440 align:middle line:84%
I have a program out called
"The Sponge Principle."

00:09:18.440 --> 00:09:20.810 align:middle line:84%
And I think that, more
than anything else,

00:09:20.810 --> 00:09:25.520 align:middle line:84%
is the real key to addressing
a situation like this.

00:09:25.520 --> 00:09:27.260 align:middle line:84%
You know what you
know and that's

00:09:27.260 --> 00:09:28.940 align:middle line:90%
what got you where you are.

00:09:28.940 --> 00:09:31.520 align:middle line:84%
You know what you don't know
and that's why you read books

00:09:31.520 --> 00:09:32.600 align:middle line:90%
and you get tapes.

00:09:32.600 --> 00:09:34.400 align:middle line:84%
But it's what you
don't know you don't

00:09:34.400 --> 00:09:37.220 align:middle line:84%
know that will kill you or
at least determine where

00:09:37.220 --> 00:09:38.510 align:middle line:90%
you go or don't go in life.

00:09:38.510 --> 00:09:41.070 align:middle line:84%
And I'm a total sponge
for information.

00:09:41.070 --> 00:09:42.950 align:middle line:84%
Especially today in
the information age,

00:09:42.950 --> 00:09:43.965 align:middle line:90%
you've got the internet.

00:09:43.965 --> 00:09:44.840 align:middle line:90%
You've got libraries.

00:09:44.840 --> 00:09:47.900 align:middle line:84%
You've got audiotapes,
videotapes, seminars.

00:09:47.900 --> 00:09:50.557 align:middle line:84%
You can become an expert
on almost anything.

00:09:50.557 --> 00:09:52.640 align:middle line:84%
I mean, literally you could
become a brain surgeon

00:09:52.640 --> 00:09:55.040 align:middle line:84%
in the next five years if
that's what you wanted to do.

00:09:55.040 --> 00:09:55.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:09:55.880 --> 00:09:57.590 align:middle line:84%
They demonstrate it on
The Learning Channel.

00:09:57.590 --> 00:09:57.950 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:09:57.950 --> 00:09:58.750 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:09:58.750 --> 00:10:02.540 align:middle line:84%
>> So "The Sponge Principle,"
the information you want to be

00:10:02.540 --> 00:10:05.930 align:middle line:84%
in your own business-- to
transition into another field--

00:10:05.930 --> 00:10:09.560 align:middle line:84%
to start again all together--
the information is out there.

00:10:09.560 --> 00:10:11.840 align:middle line:84%
And one of the absolute
key traits to success

00:10:11.840 --> 00:10:13.520 align:middle line:90%
is not to reinvent the wheel.

00:10:13.520 --> 00:10:16.220 align:middle line:84%
Go find out the
mistakes and problems

00:10:16.220 --> 00:10:19.580 align:middle line:84%
other people have solved in
that very situation you're

00:10:19.580 --> 00:10:21.395 align:middle line:90%
trying to transition into.

00:10:21.395 --> 00:10:22.970 align:middle line:10%
>> And, as you said--

00:10:22.970 --> 00:10:24.830 align:middle line:10%
we were talking about a book.

00:10:24.830 --> 00:10:27.800 align:middle line:84%
If you think there is a book in
you and you want to write that,

00:10:27.800 --> 00:10:29.720 align:middle line:84%
there is even a way that
you can self-publish.

00:10:29.720 --> 00:10:31.262 align:middle line:84%
You can go to the
library and you can

00:10:31.262 --> 00:10:32.780 align:middle line:90%
get a book on self-publishing.

00:10:32.780 --> 00:10:37.160 align:middle line:84%
There is information out there
from all the different media

00:10:37.160 --> 00:10:38.750 align:middle line:90%
that you could gain.

00:10:38.750 --> 00:10:40.550 align:middle line:90%
OK, so be a sponge.

00:10:40.550 --> 00:10:42.890 align:middle line:84%
And I love the idea
of what you said, too,

00:10:42.890 --> 00:10:44.960 align:middle line:90%
like don't limit yourself.

00:10:44.960 --> 00:10:46.550 align:middle line:10%
Don't allow limitations.

00:10:46.550 --> 00:10:48.800 align:middle line:10%
But what if you are in
a circumstance where

00:10:48.800 --> 00:10:51.650 align:middle line:10%
you don't have the support
around you of people

00:10:51.650 --> 00:10:55.640 align:middle line:10%
who are encouraging
you to do your best?

00:10:55.640 --> 00:10:58.550 align:middle line:84%
>> I think Brian Tracy, whom
I just worked with on this

00:10:58.550 --> 00:11:00.510 align:middle line:90%
previous program, said it best.

00:11:00.510 --> 00:11:02.840 align:middle line:90%
If it's to be, it's up to me.

00:11:02.840 --> 00:11:05.900 align:middle line:84%
And, certainly, we would
like to surround ourselves

00:11:05.900 --> 00:11:07.310 align:middle line:90%
with supportive people.

00:11:07.310 --> 00:11:09.680 align:middle line:84%
Certainly, we should
endeavor to look

00:11:09.680 --> 00:11:11.000 align:middle line:90%
for supportive relationships.

00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:13.530 align:middle line:84%
But, very often, they
don't happen at once.

00:11:13.530 --> 00:11:16.340 align:middle line:84%
And you have to really take
charge of your own destiny.

00:11:16.340 --> 00:11:18.620 align:middle line:90%
That's another key trait.

00:11:18.620 --> 00:11:20.060 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes the
support isn't there.

00:11:20.060 --> 00:11:22.040 align:middle line:84%
You just have to
live with this fact

00:11:22.040 --> 00:11:24.860 align:middle line:84%
that the support
isn't there, and take

00:11:24.860 --> 00:11:26.030 align:middle line:90%
charge of your own destiny.

00:11:26.030 --> 00:11:26.660 align:middle line:90%
>> I like that.

00:11:26.660 --> 00:11:27.560 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:11:27.560 --> 00:11:29.040 align:middle line:90%
Bottom line, we are responsible.

00:11:29.040 --> 00:11:29.840 align:middle line:10%
>> Absolutely.

00:11:29.840 --> 00:11:31.970 align:middle line:10%
>> We can't put it
out there against--

00:11:31.970 --> 00:11:35.090 align:middle line:10%
that someone else isn't
helping us or supporting us.

00:11:35.090 --> 00:11:36.830 align:middle line:10%
It's nice, though,
if you do have

00:11:36.830 --> 00:11:38.510 align:middle line:10%
that kind of loving support.

00:11:38.510 --> 00:11:39.580 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:11:39.580 --> 00:11:43.385 align:middle line:84%
>> I mean, the responsibility--
look at our country today.

00:11:43.385 --> 00:11:45.380 align:middle line:84%
Everything boils
down to one thing.

00:11:45.380 --> 00:11:47.720 align:middle line:84%
All the problems we see
with gangs, and drugs,

00:11:47.720 --> 00:11:50.210 align:middle line:84%
and all the negativity boil
down to people not wanting

00:11:50.210 --> 00:11:52.430 align:middle line:84%
to take responsibility
for their own actions.

00:11:52.430 --> 00:11:53.230 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:11:53.230 --> 00:11:55.820 align:middle line:84%
>> And that's why responsibility
for your own actions is

00:11:55.820 --> 00:11:58.350 align:middle line:90%
so critical to success.

00:11:58.350 --> 00:11:59.150 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:11:59.150 --> 00:12:01.580 align:middle line:84%
Well, I am so excited about
the materials that you have.

00:12:01.580 --> 00:12:02.820 align:middle line:90%
There are books and so forth.

00:12:02.820 --> 00:12:04.710 align:middle line:10%
So there is more
for us to share.

00:12:04.710 --> 00:12:07.460 align:middle line:10%
So if you will stay
tuned, we will be back.

00:12:07.460 --> 00:12:09.770 align:middle line:10%
And we are going to help
you, with Andrew Wood,

00:12:09.770 --> 00:12:12.282 align:middle line:10%
maximize your potential.

