your experience.

00:12:28.490 --> 00:12:31.820 align:middle line:84%
How was it better for you to
come to the United States?

00:12:31.820 --> 00:12:33.510 align:middle line:84%
You left England,
which we both love.

00:12:33.510 --> 00:12:34.310 align:middle line:10%
[LAUGHS]

00:12:34.310 --> 00:12:36.685 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you know, I think
England's a wonderful country.

00:12:36.685 --> 00:12:39.590 align:middle line:84%
And it's not that there
isn't opportunity in England.

00:12:39.590 --> 00:12:42.450 align:middle line:84%
But America is the land
of the American dream.

00:12:42.450 --> 00:12:44.370 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's just
so much easier here.

00:12:44.370 --> 00:12:47.990 align:middle line:84%
The people are more receptive
to the entrepreneurial spirit

00:12:47.990 --> 00:12:49.910 align:middle line:84%
here than they are
anywhere else in the world.

00:12:49.910 --> 00:12:50.710 align:middle line:90%
>> I think so.

00:12:50.710 --> 00:12:51.950 align:middle line:84%
>> And that really
gives you the edge.

00:12:51.950 --> 00:12:52.130 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:12:52.130 --> 00:12:53.310 align:middle line:90%
I see that with people.

00:12:53.310 --> 00:12:55.430 align:middle line:84%
The enthusiasm of
the individual--

00:12:55.430 --> 00:12:58.400 align:middle line:84%
there is an individualist
quality to the entrepreneur.

00:12:58.400 --> 00:13:00.770 align:middle line:90%
And it really is admired.

00:13:00.770 --> 00:13:04.580 align:middle line:84%
In the book, tell us a little
bit more about your story.

00:13:04.580 --> 00:13:08.125 align:middle line:84%
You had some difficulties
as you moved through this.

00:13:08.125 --> 00:13:09.500 align:middle line:84%
I know one of the
things you said

00:13:09.500 --> 00:13:10.970 align:middle line:84%
was you moved to
California and you

00:13:10.970 --> 00:13:13.580 align:middle line:84%
were supposed to be moving
into a job with a friend

00:13:13.580 --> 00:13:14.870 align:middle line:90%
with a limousine service.

00:13:14.870 --> 00:13:17.040 align:middle line:84%
>> I had originally
moved out to California.

00:13:17.040 --> 00:13:19.707 align:middle line:84%
I had a golf scholarship down in
West Palm Beach Junior College.

00:13:19.707 --> 00:13:21.373 align:middle line:10%
And then, when that
was kind of through,

00:13:21.373 --> 00:13:23.480 align:middle line:10%
I moved out to California
to drive a limo.

00:13:23.480 --> 00:13:25.880 align:middle line:84%
And within about four weeks,
the business went under.

00:13:25.880 --> 00:13:27.800 align:middle line:84%
And that's how I
accidentally got involved

00:13:27.800 --> 00:13:29.210 align:middle line:90%
in the karate business.

00:13:29.210 --> 00:13:32.600 align:middle line:84%
And I was fortunate in
the karate business.

00:13:32.600 --> 00:13:34.580 align:middle line:84%
I bought a school
off my instructor,

00:13:34.580 --> 00:13:38.390 align:middle line:84%
and wasn't quite making
enough money to live.

00:13:38.390 --> 00:13:40.890 align:middle line:84%
And so I did what everybody
else in the karate business did.

00:13:40.890 --> 00:13:42.270 align:middle line:84%
I opened another
school, figuring

00:13:42.270 --> 00:13:43.980 align:middle line:84%
that if I didn't make
quite enough money in one

00:13:43.980 --> 00:13:46.272 align:middle line:84%
business and not quite enough
money in another business

00:13:46.272 --> 00:13:48.717 align:middle line:84%
and put them together,
then that would work.

00:13:48.717 --> 00:13:49.800 align:middle line:90%
And, of course, it didn't.

00:13:49.800 --> 00:13:52.290 align:middle line:84%
And that's really when I came
up with this idea of "The Sponge

00:13:52.290 --> 00:13:53.090 align:middle line:90%
Principle."

00:13:53.090 --> 00:13:55.990 align:middle line:84%
And what I did was I sat down
with a piece of paper and said,

00:13:55.990 --> 00:13:57.240 align:middle line:90%
is this what I want to do?

00:13:57.240 --> 00:13:58.440 align:middle line:90%
The answer was yes.

00:13:58.440 --> 00:13:59.790 align:middle line:90%
Why can't I do it?

00:13:59.790 --> 00:14:01.650 align:middle line:84%
Because I don't
understand the first thing

00:14:01.650 --> 00:14:03.880 align:middle line:84%
about running a business or
advertising or marketing.

00:14:03.880 --> 00:14:04.680 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:14:04.680 --> 00:14:06.055 align:middle line:84%
>> I went to the
local bookstore.

00:14:06.055 --> 00:14:08.590 align:middle line:84%
I bought 28 books on
how to design an ad.

00:14:08.590 --> 00:14:09.390 align:middle line:90%
>> Whoa.

00:14:09.390 --> 00:14:10.190 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:14:10.190 --> 00:14:11.430 align:middle line:90%
>> Read them all in a month.

00:14:11.430 --> 00:14:13.580 align:middle line:84%
Literally, in one month,
I read a book a day,

00:14:13.580 --> 00:14:15.030 align:middle line:90%
underlining, highlighting.

00:14:15.030 --> 00:14:17.400 align:middle line:84%
I went back into my karate
business, redesigned

00:14:17.400 --> 00:14:20.890 align:middle line:84%
the first ad I ever did in my
life that actually made sense.

00:14:20.890 --> 00:14:21.690 align:middle line:90%
Bingo.

00:14:21.690 --> 00:14:23.040 align:middle line:90%
The phone started ringing.

00:14:23.040 --> 00:14:24.425 align:middle line:90%
So I thought, well, gee.

00:14:24.425 --> 00:14:25.800 align:middle line:84%
If I can learn
about advertising,

00:14:25.800 --> 00:14:27.870 align:middle line:84%
maybe I could learn
about sales like that.

00:14:27.870 --> 00:14:29.670 align:middle line:84%
Went back-- all of
a sudden, now when

00:14:29.670 --> 00:14:32.120 align:middle line:84%
people called I actually
was able to sign them up.

00:14:32.120 --> 00:14:34.740 align:middle line:84%
And, literally, within a
period of about six months,

00:14:34.740 --> 00:14:39.600 align:middle line:84%
I went from making $7,000 a
year to making $7,000 or $8,000

00:14:39.600 --> 00:14:40.730 align:middle line:90%
a month.

00:14:40.730 --> 00:14:43.140 align:middle line:84%
And that's a pretty
significant financial change.

00:14:43.140 --> 00:14:45.840 align:middle line:10%
>> [LAUGHS] Well, you
obviously found, then,

00:14:45.840 --> 00:14:49.240 align:middle line:10%
techniques that absolutely work
and that's what you're sharing

00:14:49.240 --> 00:14:50.040 align:middle line:10%
through your--

00:14:50.040 --> 00:14:50.970 align:middle line:10%
>> That's what I've tried
to do in "Making it Big."

00:14:50.970 --> 00:14:51.300 align:middle line:90%
>> --tapes and things.

00:14:51.300 --> 00:14:52.100 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:14:52.100 --> 00:14:55.770 align:middle line:84%
>> It's very much a
step-by-step process.

00:14:55.770 --> 00:14:57.270 align:middle line:90%
It's not a feel good thing.

00:14:57.270 --> 00:14:59.820 align:middle line:84%
It's, OK, this is what
you need to do if you

00:14:59.820 --> 00:15:02.020 align:middle line:90%
want to get from here to there.

00:15:02.020 --> 00:15:03.540 align:middle line:84%
And there are
essentially 12 traits,

00:15:03.540 --> 00:15:06.290 align:middle line:84%
starting with big dreams
and ending with persistence.

00:15:06.290 --> 00:15:09.330 align:middle line:84%
And probably the
two most important,

00:15:09.330 --> 00:15:13.080 align:middle line:84%
other than those two, are
setting goals for yourself

00:15:13.080 --> 00:15:16.080 align:middle line:84%
and understanding how
to solve problems.

00:15:16.080 --> 00:15:18.180 align:middle line:84%
Problem solving is
really the master skill

00:15:18.180 --> 00:15:20.670 align:middle line:84%
of life, in that
where you are today

00:15:20.670 --> 00:15:22.830 align:middle line:84%
and your ability to get
where you want to go

00:15:22.830 --> 00:15:26.970 align:middle line:84%
is completely related to your
ability to solve problems.

00:15:26.970 --> 00:15:29.340 align:middle line:84%
If you can solve
problems, you immediately

00:15:29.340 --> 00:15:30.630 align:middle line:90%
graduate to bigger problems.

00:15:30.630 --> 00:15:31.430 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS]

00:15:31.430 --> 00:15:34.400 align:middle line:84%
>> And the bigger problems you
graduate to, the better you do

00:15:34.400 --> 00:15:35.200 align:middle line:90%
it.

00:15:35.200 --> 00:15:36.660 align:middle line:84%
Because if you're
not doing very well,

00:15:36.660 --> 00:15:38.010 align:middle line:90%
then your problems are meager.

00:15:38.010 --> 00:15:41.490 align:middle line:84%
You just have to find
enough money to eat or live.

00:15:41.490 --> 00:15:43.680 align:middle line:84%
It's when you really
become good at problem

00:15:43.680 --> 00:15:46.030 align:middle line:84%
solving that your problems
become very complex.

00:15:46.030 --> 00:15:47.890 align:middle line:84%
And that's when you
know you're doing good.

00:15:47.890 --> 00:15:48.690 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:15:48.690 --> 00:15:50.520 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] So you will
get bigger problems

00:15:50.520 --> 00:15:51.510 align:middle line:90%
that you'll be able to solve.

00:15:51.510 --> 00:15:52.310 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:15:52.310 --> 00:15:53.820 align:middle line:90%
>> [LAUGHS] That is progress.

00:15:53.820 --> 00:15:54.620 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:15:54.620 --> 00:15:58.890 align:middle line:84%
So, from that, you have
found, then, that there are--

00:15:58.890 --> 00:16:00.660 align:middle line:84%
and you have a
series of CDs, too.

00:16:00.660 --> 00:16:02.790 align:middle line:84%
In addition to "The
Sponge Principle,"

00:16:02.790 --> 00:16:04.200 align:middle line:90%
"The Legendary Leadership."

00:16:04.200 --> 00:16:08.400 align:middle line:84%
Now you have a series on the
traits of power, influence

00:16:08.400 --> 00:16:09.310 align:middle line:90%
and effectiveness.

00:16:09.310 --> 00:16:10.800 align:middle line:84%
Now, in this series
that you have

00:16:10.800 --> 00:16:15.000 align:middle line:84%
done, what you're talking
about is the successful people,

00:16:15.000 --> 00:16:17.800 align:middle line:84%
