00:16:17.800 --> 00:16:18.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:16:18.600 --> 00:16:20.550 align:middle line:84%
I've done a tremendous
amount of research,

00:16:20.550 --> 00:16:22.680 align:middle line:90%
both in person and in reading.

00:16:22.680 --> 00:16:24.840 align:middle line:84%
Hundreds and hundreds
of biographies

00:16:24.840 --> 00:16:26.730 align:middle line:90%
and studying famous people.

00:16:26.730 --> 00:16:29.490 align:middle line:84%
And legendary leadership
is a very important skill

00:16:29.490 --> 00:16:31.830 align:middle line:84%
because we are all
leaders to somebody.

00:16:31.830 --> 00:16:33.270 align:middle line:90%
We are leaders to our family.

00:16:33.270 --> 00:16:35.220 align:middle line:84%
We might be leaders to
the little league team.

00:16:35.220 --> 00:16:37.470 align:middle line:84%
We might be leaders to
schoolchildren, whatever.

00:16:37.470 --> 00:16:39.900 align:middle line:84%
So understanding leadership
is a very important skill

00:16:39.900 --> 00:16:41.080 align:middle line:90%
for everybody.

00:16:41.080 --> 00:16:42.900 align:middle line:84%
And what I've done is
studied these traits

00:16:42.900 --> 00:16:48.018 align:middle line:84%
of what is it that causes us
to follow and influence people.

00:16:48.018 --> 00:16:50.310 align:middle line:84%
And the traits on "Legendary
Leadership"-- again, there

00:16:50.310 --> 00:16:52.390 align:middle line:84%
are 12 traits that are
slightly different.

00:16:52.390 --> 00:16:54.660 align:middle line:84%
But the first of those
traits is vision.

00:16:54.660 --> 00:16:56.300 align:middle line:84%
What is it you
want to accomplish?

00:16:56.300 --> 00:16:57.510 align:middle line:90%
Where is it you want to go?

00:16:57.510 --> 00:17:00.960 align:middle line:84%
Where do you want to
lead your team to?

00:17:00.960 --> 00:17:03.210 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I know we've talked
with people who work with

00:17:03.210 --> 00:17:03.750 align:middle line:90%
businesses.

00:17:03.750 --> 00:17:06.240 align:middle line:10%
They go in and they say, the
first thing you have to do

00:17:06.240 --> 00:17:08.040 align:middle line:10%
is write your vision statement.

00:17:08.040 --> 00:17:09.950 align:middle line:84%
You need to know
where you're going,

00:17:09.950 --> 00:17:13.510 align:middle line:84%
and what you want to do,
OK, or a mission statement.

00:17:13.510 --> 00:17:16.140 align:middle line:84%
And so we need to do
that as individuals

00:17:16.140 --> 00:17:18.589 align:middle line:84%
in any part of our lives--
know what it is we want.

00:17:18.589 --> 00:17:19.389 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:17:19.389 --> 00:17:22.230 align:middle line:84%
Well, we have to have an
understanding of where

00:17:22.230 --> 00:17:24.690 align:middle line:84%
it is we want to be,
if you don't like

00:17:24.690 --> 00:17:28.319 align:middle line:84%
and are just absolutely ecstatic
about where we are right now.

00:17:28.319 --> 00:17:29.560 align:middle line:90%
And so that's important.

00:17:29.560 --> 00:17:31.680 align:middle line:84%
And then the second trait
of legendary leaders,

00:17:31.680 --> 00:17:36.310 align:middle line:84%
which is also very applicable
to personal success, is passion.

00:17:36.310 --> 00:17:38.910 align:middle line:84%
You have to be passionate
about achieving this vision.

00:17:38.910 --> 00:17:40.710 align:middle line:90%
If the vision is not yours--

00:17:40.710 --> 00:17:43.500 align:middle line:84%
if the vision is not something
you're passionate about,

00:17:43.500 --> 00:17:45.990 align:middle line:84%
then you're not going to
make the sacrifice or put

00:17:45.990 --> 00:17:49.290 align:middle line:84%
in the hard work-- and, believe
me, you have to do both--

00:17:49.290 --> 00:17:51.680 align:middle line:84%
in order to get what it
where it is you want to go.

00:17:51.680 --> 00:17:54.870 align:middle line:84%
>> And, you know, that is the
one thing that I find with

00:17:54.870 --> 00:17:56.730 align:middle line:84%
people that I interview
for this show.

00:17:56.730 --> 00:17:58.260 align:middle line:90%
They do have a passion.

00:17:58.260 --> 00:18:00.150 align:middle line:84%
And you and I talked
about that earlier.

00:18:00.150 --> 00:18:03.330 align:middle line:84%
They are driven to do it
because it is so important,

00:18:03.330 --> 00:18:05.790 align:middle line:84%
and it works so well, and
it helps so many people.

00:18:05.790 --> 00:18:07.140 align:middle line:90%
They can't help but do it.

00:18:07.140 --> 00:18:08.307 align:middle line:90%
That's that kind of feeling.

00:18:08.307 --> 00:18:11.580 align:middle line:84%
>> And a lot of people simply
don't know what their passion

00:18:11.580 --> 00:18:12.690 align:middle line:90%
is.

00:18:12.690 --> 00:18:15.960 align:middle line:84%
You ask nine people out of
10, what is it you want to do?

00:18:15.960 --> 00:18:17.460 align:middle line:90%
Gee, I don't know.

00:18:17.460 --> 00:18:19.590 align:middle line:84%
They literally spend
more time thinking

00:18:19.590 --> 00:18:21.893 align:middle line:84%
about where they're going
to go on vacation than they

00:18:21.893 --> 00:18:24.060 align:middle line:84%
do what they want to do
with the rest of their life.

00:18:24.060 --> 00:18:25.830 align:middle line:90%
It's really amazing.

00:18:25.830 --> 00:18:27.480 align:middle line:84%
>> And, how do you
get them, then,

00:18:27.480 --> 00:18:30.540 align:middle line:84%
from the vacation
to their career?

00:18:30.540 --> 00:18:32.850 align:middle line:84%
How do you move the people
from-- they understand

00:18:32.850 --> 00:18:34.080 align:middle line:90%
that, oh, I want to do this.

00:18:34.080 --> 00:18:35.040 align:middle line:90%
I love to do this.

00:18:35.040 --> 00:18:36.360 align:middle line:90%
I want to be in Hawaii.

00:18:36.360 --> 00:18:39.450 align:middle line:84%
But how do we move that
kind of energy into career?

00:18:39.450 --> 00:18:42.120 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you know, a lot of
times people simply don't know

00:18:42.120 --> 00:18:44.610 align:middle line:84%
what they want to do
because, as Henry Ford said,

00:18:44.610 --> 00:18:46.410 align:middle line:84%
thinking is the
hardest work there is.

00:18:46.410 --> 00:18:47.970 align:middle line:90%
They've never sat down.

00:18:47.970 --> 00:18:50.790 align:middle line:84%
And I often find in
my seminars that when

00:18:50.790 --> 00:18:53.040 align:middle line:84%
people say that to me, I
kind of reverse it on them

00:18:53.040 --> 00:18:55.890 align:middle line:84%
and say, OK, what is it
you don't want to do?

00:18:55.890 --> 00:18:58.380 align:middle line:84%
Do you want to go down the
coal mines and dig for coal

00:18:58.380 --> 00:19:01.635 align:middle line:84%
or do you want to pick
up garbage for a living?

00:19:01.635 --> 00:19:03.698 align:middle line:84%
If you can't figure out
what you want to do,

00:19:03.698 --> 00:19:05.990 align:middle line:84%
start listing the whole of
things you don't want to do.

00:19:05.990 --> 00:19:06.280 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:19:06.280 --> 00:19:08.360 align:middle line:84%
And see what's left
at the end of the day.

00:19:08.360 --> 00:19:09.160 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:19:09.160 --> 00:19:12.720 align:middle line:84%
So that is reverse psychology
that will work on that.

00:19:12.720 --> 00:19:19.560 align:middle line:84%
And as people start to like look
inside and say, OK, what is it,

00:19:19.560 --> 00:19:21.060 align:middle line:84%
they really are
accomplishing a lot.

00:19:21.060 --> 00:19:22.890 align:middle line:84%
Because they're getting
to know themselves.

00:19:22.890 --> 00:19:23.690 align:middle line:90%
Are they not?

00:19:23.690 --> 00:19:26.000 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's a real
positive step, too.

00:19:26.000 --> 00:19:26.800 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, absolutely.

00:19:26.800 --> 00:19:31.890 align:middle line:84%
I think the process of actually
just sitting down and really

00:19:31.890 --> 00:19:33.960 align:middle line:90%
